[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1272},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment\u002F":1247,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment\u002F":1256},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20220118\u002F1578337381\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1232,"date":1233,"description":1234,"extension":1235,"lang":1236,"meta":1237,"navigation":99,"path":1238,"readingMinutes":1239,"seo":1240,"standalone":1241,"stem":1242,"tags":1243,"tldr":1244,"updated":1233,"url":1245,"__hash__":1246},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment.md","The JavaScript a = b = c Interview Question, Finally Explained","1001639236",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1227},"minimark",[11,16,25,29,32,116,119,145,148,248,251,345,353,409,416,445,452,510,516,678,681,766,769,776,782,788,795,801,808,833,836,859,869,875,882,887,912,915,938,958,960,985,1008,1033,1075,1084,1090,1169,1172,1178,1181,1200,1204,1223],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"Multiple left-hand assignment — chain variable assignments, if you prefer — is one of those JavaScript interview questions that shows up over and over. Stuff like ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"a = b = c",", which looks harmless but somehow makes everyone second-guess themselves. So I figured I'd write a post on how this thing actually works.",[12,26,28],{"id":27},"multiple-left-hand-assignment","Multiple left-hand assignment",[17,30,31],{},"\"Multiple left-hand assignment\" basically means chaining assignments together. You've probably seen a question like this:",[33,34,39],"pre",{"className":35,"code":36,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","var a = 1;\nvar b = 2;\nvar c = 3;\n\na = b = c;\n","js","",[21,40,41,64,79,94,101],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,43,46,50,54,57,61],"span",{"class":44,"line":45},"line",1,[42,47,49],{"class":48},"sWyjQ","var",[42,51,53],{"class":52},"sMAXC"," a ",[42,55,56],{"class":48},"=",[42,58,60],{"class":59},"sCcAr"," 1",[42,62,63],{"class":52},";\n",[42,65,67,69,72,74,77],{"class":44,"line":66},2,[42,68,49],{"class":48},[42,70,71],{"class":52}," b ",[42,73,56],{"class":48},[42,75,76],{"class":59}," 2",[42,78,63],{"class":52},[42,80,82,84,87,89,92],{"class":44,"line":81},3,[42,83,49],{"class":48},[42,85,86],{"class":52}," c ",[42,88,56],{"class":48},[42,90,91],{"class":59}," 3",[42,93,63],{"class":52},[42,95,97],{"class":44,"line":96},4,[42,98,100],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":99},true,"\n",[42,102,104,107,109,111,113],{"class":44,"line":103},5,[42,105,106],{"class":52},"a ",[42,108,56],{"class":48},[42,110,71],{"class":52},[42,112,56],{"class":48},[42,114,115],{"class":52}," c;\n",[17,117,118],{},"On the surface it's pretty simple, but there's actually a decent amount of concept packed in here.",[17,120,121,122,124,125,128,129,132,133,136,137,140,141,144],{},"The thing is, the assignment operator (",[21,123,56],{},") is right-associative. So ",[21,126,127],{},"c"," gets assigned into ",[21,130,131],{},"b"," first, and that assignment is itself an expression — meaning ",[21,134,135],{},"a"," ends up swallowing the result of the ",[21,138,139],{},"b = c"," expression, which is ",[21,142,143],{},"3",".",[17,146,147],{},"If you break it apart, it looks like this:",[33,149,151],{"className":35,"code":150,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var a = 1;\nvar b = 2;\nvar c = 3;\n\na = (b = c);\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F 3\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F 3\nconsole.log(c); \u002F\u002F 3\n",[21,152,153,165,177,189,193,207,224,236],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,154,155,157,159,161,163],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,156,49],{"class":48},[42,158,53],{"class":52},[42,160,56],{"class":48},[42,162,60],{"class":59},[42,164,63],{"class":52},[42,166,167,169,171,173,175],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,168,49],{"class":48},[42,170,71],{"class":52},[42,172,56],{"class":48},[42,174,76],{"class":59},[42,176,63],{"class":52},[42,178,179,181,183,185,187],{"class":44,"line":81},[42,180,49],{"class":48},[42,182,86],{"class":52},[42,184,56],{"class":48},[42,186,91],{"class":59},[42,188,63],{"class":52},[42,190,191],{"class":44,"line":96},[42,192,100],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":99},[42,194,195,197,199,202,204],{"class":44,"line":103},[42,196,106],{"class":52},[42,198,56],{"class":48},[42,200,201],{"class":52}," (b ",[42,203,56],{"class":48},[42,205,206],{"class":52}," c);\n",[42,208,210,213,217,220],{"class":44,"line":209},6,[42,211,212],{"class":52},"console.",[42,214,216],{"class":215},"sj_SG","log",[42,218,219],{"class":52},"(a); ",[42,221,223],{"class":222},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F 3\n",[42,225,227,229,231,234],{"class":44,"line":226},7,[42,228,212],{"class":52},[42,230,216],{"class":215},[42,232,233],{"class":52},"(b); ",[42,235,223],{"class":222},[42,237,239,241,243,246],{"class":44,"line":238},8,[42,240,212],{"class":52},[42,242,216],{"class":215},[42,244,245],{"class":52},"(c); ",[42,247,223],{"class":222},[17,249,250],{},"Or you can think of it this way:",[33,252,254],{"className":35,"code":253,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var a = 1;\nvar b = 2;\nvar c = 3;\n\nb = c;\na = b;\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F 3\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F 3\nconsole.log(c); \u002F\u002F 3\n",[21,255,256,268,280,292,296,305,314,324,334],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,257,258,260,262,264,266],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,259,49],{"class":48},[42,261,53],{"class":52},[42,263,56],{"class":48},[42,265,60],{"class":59},[42,267,63],{"class":52},[42,269,270,272,274,276,278],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,271,49],{"class":48},[42,273,71],{"class":52},[42,275,56],{"class":48},[42,277,76],{"class":59},[42,279,63],{"class":52},[42,281,282,284,286,288,290],{"class":44,"line":81},[42,283,49],{"class":48},[42,285,86],{"class":52},[42,287,56],{"class":48},[42,289,91],{"class":59},[42,291,63],{"class":52},[42,293,294],{"class":44,"line":96},[42,295,100],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":99},[42,297,298,301,303],{"class":44,"line":103},[42,299,300],{"class":52},"b ",[42,302,56],{"class":48},[42,304,115],{"class":52},[42,306,307,309,311],{"class":44,"line":209},[42,308,106],{"class":52},[42,310,56],{"class":48},[42,312,313],{"class":52}," b;\n",[42,315,316,318,320,322],{"class":44,"line":226},[42,317,212],{"class":52},[42,319,216],{"class":215},[42,321,219],{"class":52},[42,323,223],{"class":222},[42,325,326,328,330,332],{"class":44,"line":238},[42,327,212],{"class":52},[42,329,216],{"class":215},[42,331,233],{"class":52},[42,333,223],{"class":222},[42,335,337,339,341,343],{"class":44,"line":336},9,[42,338,212],{"class":52},[42,340,216],{"class":215},[42,342,245],{"class":52},[42,344,223],{"class":222},[17,346,347,348,352],{},"But JavaScript is a beautiful (",[349,350,351],"del",{},"infuriating",") language, and you only need to tweak the question slightly to turn it into a brand new one:",[33,354,356],{"className":35,"code":355,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var a = b = c = 1;\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F 1\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F 1\nconsole.log(c); \u002F\u002F 1\n",[21,357,358,378,389,399],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,359,360,362,364,366,368,370,372,374,376],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,361,49],{"class":48},[42,363,53],{"class":52},[42,365,56],{"class":48},[42,367,71],{"class":52},[42,369,56],{"class":48},[42,371,86],{"class":52},[42,373,56],{"class":48},[42,375,60],{"class":59},[42,377,63],{"class":52},[42,379,380,382,384,386],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,381,212],{"class":52},[42,383,216],{"class":215},[42,385,219],{"class":52},[42,387,388],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F 1\n",[42,390,391,393,395,397],{"class":44,"line":81},[42,392,212],{"class":52},[42,394,216],{"class":215},[42,396,233],{"class":52},[42,398,388],{"class":222},[42,400,401,403,405,407],{"class":44,"line":96},[42,402,212],{"class":52},[42,404,216],{"class":215},[42,406,245],{"class":52},[42,408,388],{"class":222},[17,410,411,412,415],{},"So this one \"multiple left-hand assignment\" idea can actually exercise a ton of concepts in JavaScript. Take that ",[21,413,414],{},"var a = b = c = 1;"," — you can read it as:",[33,417,419],{"className":35,"code":418,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var var1 = (var2 = (var3 = 1));\n",[21,420,421],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,422,423,425,428,430,433,435,438,440,442],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,424,49],{"class":48},[42,426,427],{"class":52}," var1 ",[42,429,56],{"class":48},[42,431,432],{"class":52}," (var2 ",[42,434,56],{"class":48},[42,436,437],{"class":52}," (var3 ",[42,439,56],{"class":48},[42,441,60],{"class":59},[42,443,444],{"class":52},"));\n",[17,446,447,448,451],{},"The result is ",[21,449,450],{},"1"," across the board. But tweak the question just a little more and you'll hit something weird:",[33,453,455],{"className":35,"code":454,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"console.log(a); \u002F\u002F undefined\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F ReferenceError: b is not defined\nconsole.log(c); \u002F\u002F never runs because of the error above\nvar a = b = c = 1;\n",[21,456,457,468,479,490],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,458,459,461,463,465],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,460,212],{"class":52},[42,462,216],{"class":215},[42,464,219],{"class":52},[42,466,467],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F undefined\n",[42,469,470,472,474,476],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,471,212],{"class":52},[42,473,216],{"class":215},[42,475,233],{"class":52},[42,477,478],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F ReferenceError: b is not defined\n",[42,480,481,483,485,487],{"class":44,"line":81},[42,482,212],{"class":52},[42,484,216],{"class":215},[42,486,245],{"class":52},[42,488,489],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F never runs because of the error above\n",[42,491,492,494,496,498,500,502,504,506,508],{"class":44,"line":96},[42,493,49],{"class":48},[42,495,53],{"class":52},[42,497,56],{"class":48},[42,499,71],{"class":52},[42,501,56],{"class":48},[42,503,86],{"class":52},[42,505,56],{"class":48},[42,507,60],{"class":59},[42,509,63],{"class":52},[17,511,512,513,515],{},"So where's the problem here? It comes down to hoisting from the ",[21,514,49],{}," syntax. You can use the creation-phase \u002F execution-phase model to pull it apart:",[33,517,519],{"className":35,"code":518,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"\u002F\u002F Original code\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F undefined\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F ReferenceError: b is not defined\nconsole.log(c); \u002F\u002F never runs because of the error above\nvar a = b = c = 1;\n\n\u002F\u002F Creation phase\n\u002F\u002F var gets hoisted, so only a is hoisted\nvar a;\n\n\u002F\u002F Execution phase\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F a was hoisted and given a default memory slot, so we get \"undefined\"\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F at this point b was never declared or assigned, so \"ReferenceError: b is not defined\"\n\u002F\u002F the error stops execution here\nconsole.log(c);\nc = 1;\nb = c;\na = b;\n",[21,520,521,526,536,546,556,576,580,585,590,597,602,608,620,632,638,648,660,669],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,522,523],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,524,525],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F Original code\n",[42,527,528,530,532,534],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,529,212],{"class":52},[42,531,216],{"class":215},[42,533,219],{"class":52},[42,535,467],{"class":222},[42,537,538,540,542,544],{"class":44,"line":81},[42,539,212],{"class":52},[42,541,216],{"class":215},[42,543,233],{"class":52},[42,545,478],{"class":222},[42,547,548,550,552,554],{"class":44,"line":96},[42,549,212],{"class":52},[42,551,216],{"class":215},[42,553,245],{"class":52},[42,555,489],{"class":222},[42,557,558,560,562,564,566,568,570,572,574],{"class":44,"line":103},[42,559,49],{"class":48},[42,561,53],{"class":52},[42,563,56],{"class":48},[42,565,71],{"class":52},[42,567,56],{"class":48},[42,569,86],{"class":52},[42,571,56],{"class":48},[42,573,60],{"class":59},[42,575,63],{"class":52},[42,577,578],{"class":44,"line":209},[42,579,100],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":99},[42,581,582],{"class":44,"line":226},[42,583,584],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F Creation phase\n",[42,586,587],{"class":44,"line":238},[42,588,589],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F var gets hoisted, so only a is hoisted\n",[42,591,592,594],{"class":44,"line":336},[42,593,49],{"class":48},[42,595,596],{"class":52}," a;\n",[42,598,600],{"class":44,"line":599},10,[42,601,100],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":99},[42,603,605],{"class":44,"line":604},11,[42,606,607],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F Execution phase\n",[42,609,611,613,615,617],{"class":44,"line":610},12,[42,612,212],{"class":52},[42,614,216],{"class":215},[42,616,219],{"class":52},[42,618,619],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F a was hoisted and given a default memory slot, so we get \"undefined\"\n",[42,621,623,625,627,629],{"class":44,"line":622},13,[42,624,212],{"class":52},[42,626,216],{"class":215},[42,628,233],{"class":52},[42,630,631],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F at this point b was never declared or assigned, so \"ReferenceError: b is not defined\"\n",[42,633,635],{"class":44,"line":634},14,[42,636,637],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F the error stops execution here\n",[42,639,641,643,645],{"class":44,"line":640},15,[42,642,212],{"class":52},[42,644,216],{"class":215},[42,646,647],{"class":52},"(c);\n",[42,649,651,654,656,658],{"class":44,"line":650},16,[42,652,653],{"class":52},"c ",[42,655,56],{"class":48},[42,657,60],{"class":59},[42,659,63],{"class":52},[42,661,663,665,667],{"class":44,"line":662},17,[42,664,300],{"class":52},[42,666,56],{"class":48},[42,668,115],{"class":52},[42,670,672,674,676],{"class":44,"line":671},18,[42,673,106],{"class":52},[42,675,56],{"class":48},[42,677,313],{"class":52},[17,679,680],{},"Now let's pull in a question from Hexschool's JavaScript core course:",[33,682,684],{"className":35,"code":683,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var a = { x: 1 };\nvar b = a;\na.x = { x: 2};\na.y = a = { y: 1};\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F result?\nconsole.log(b); \u002F\u002F result?\n",[21,685,686,702,712,727,745,756],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,687,688,690,692,694,697,699],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,689,49],{"class":48},[42,691,53],{"class":52},[42,693,56],{"class":48},[42,695,696],{"class":52}," { x: ",[42,698,450],{"class":59},[42,700,701],{"class":52}," };\n",[42,703,704,706,708,710],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,705,49],{"class":48},[42,707,71],{"class":52},[42,709,56],{"class":48},[42,711,596],{"class":52},[42,713,714,717,719,721,724],{"class":44,"line":81},[42,715,716],{"class":52},"a.x ",[42,718,56],{"class":48},[42,720,696],{"class":52},[42,722,723],{"class":59},"2",[42,725,726],{"class":52},"};\n",[42,728,729,732,734,736,738,741,743],{"class":44,"line":96},[42,730,731],{"class":52},"a.y ",[42,733,56],{"class":48},[42,735,53],{"class":52},[42,737,56],{"class":48},[42,739,740],{"class":52}," { y: ",[42,742,450],{"class":59},[42,744,726],{"class":52},[42,746,747,749,751,753],{"class":44,"line":103},[42,748,212],{"class":52},[42,750,216],{"class":215},[42,752,219],{"class":52},[42,754,755],{"class":222},"\u002F\u002F result?\n",[42,757,758,760,762,764],{"class":44,"line":209},[42,759,212],{"class":52},[42,761,216],{"class":215},[42,763,233],{"class":52},[42,765,755],{"class":222},[17,767,768],{},"We all know JavaScript uses call-by-sharing, so objects work by passing references around. Let's walk through this question step by step.",[17,770,771],{},[772,773],"img",{"alt":774,"src":775},"Step one","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-18%2009.57.40.png",[17,777,778],{},[772,779],{"alt":780,"src":781},"Step two","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-18%2009.58.39.png",[17,783,784],{},[772,785],{"alt":786,"src":787},"Step three","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-18%2010.01.10.png",[17,789,790,791,794],{},"Step four is where it gets a little trickier. Let's just look at the ",[21,792,793],{},"a = { y: 1 }"," part for now.",[17,796,797],{},[772,798],{"alt":799,"src":800},"Step four","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-18%2010.09.43.png",[17,802,803,804,807],{},"Okay, let's pause for a second. Earlier I talked through how to break down \"multiple left-hand assignment,\" so when you look at that last line ",[21,805,806],{},"a.y = a = { y: 1};"," you might unconsciously break it apart like this:",[33,809,811],{"className":35,"code":810,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"a = { y: 1};\na.y = a;\n",[21,812,813,825],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,814,815,817,819,821,823],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,816,106],{"class":52},[42,818,56],{"class":48},[42,820,740],{"class":52},[42,822,450],{"class":59},[42,824,726],{"class":52},[42,826,827,829,831],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,828,731],{"class":52},[42,830,56],{"class":48},[42,832,596],{"class":52},[17,834,835],{},"Or like this:",[33,837,839],{"className":35,"code":838,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"a.y = (a = { y: 1});\n",[21,840,841],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,842,843,845,847,850,852,854,856],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,844,731],{"class":52},[42,846,56],{"class":48},[42,848,849],{"class":52}," (a ",[42,851,56],{"class":48},[42,853,740],{"class":52},[42,855,450],{"class":59},[42,857,858],{"class":52},"});\n",[17,860,861,862,865,866,144],{},"So you might excitedly say ",[21,863,864],{},"console.log(a);"," is super easy — the answer is ",[21,867,868],{},"{ y: 1 }",[17,870,871],{},[772,872],{"alt":873,"src":874},"console.log(a) result","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-18%2010.22.42.png",[17,876,877,878,881],{},"But ",[21,879,880],{},"console.log(b)"," is a bit harder. Let's look back at the table:",[17,883,884],{},[772,885],{"alt":886,"src":874},"Step five",[17,888,889,890,892,893,896,897,900,901,903,904,907,908,911],{},"We can see ",[21,891,131],{}," is still pointing at ",[21,894,895],{},"0x01",", and the ",[21,898,899],{},"x"," inside ",[21,902,895],{}," points at ",[21,905,906],{},"0x02",", so one of them has to be ",[21,909,910],{},"{ x: { x: 2 } }","!",[17,913,914],{},"Wait — did you catch that? Why did I say \"one of them\"? Because there's definitely something sneaky going on here.",[17,916,917,918,920,921,923,924,927,928,931,932,934,935,937],{},"The main reason is that ",[21,919,806],{}," is really sneaky. Things aren't as simple as they look. You might think ",[21,922,135],{}," gets assigned a new memory slot ",[21,925,926],{},"0x03",", then we add a property called ",[21,929,930],{},"y"," to ",[21,933,135],{}," pointing at ",[21,936,926],{}," — after all, you probably broke it down like this:",[33,939,940],{"className":35,"code":838,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},[21,941,942],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,943,944,946,948,950,952,954,956],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,945,731],{"class":52},[42,947,56],{"class":48},[42,949,849],{"class":52},[42,951,56],{"class":48},[42,953,740],{"class":52},[42,955,450],{"class":59},[42,957,858],{"class":52},[17,959,835],{},[33,961,963],{"className":35,"code":962,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"a = { y: 1 };\na.y = a;\n",[21,964,965,977],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,966,967,969,971,973,975],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,968,106],{"class":52},[42,970,56],{"class":48},[42,972,740],{"class":52},[42,974,450],{"class":59},[42,976,701],{"class":52},[42,978,979,981,983],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,980,731],{"class":52},[42,982,56],{"class":48},[42,984,596],{"class":52},[17,986,987,988,990,991,994,995,997,998,1000,1001,1003,1004,1007],{},"But that's wrong. So let's first look at operator precedence and associativity in JavaScript. The member-access operator (",[21,989,144],{},") has very high precedence, so ",[21,992,993],{},"a.y"," definitely gets evaluated first. At that moment ",[21,996,135],{}," hasn't been overwritten yet, so the ",[21,999,135],{}," we resolve still holds its original memory slot — ",[21,1002,895],{},". The property doesn't have a value yet, so JavaScript defaults it to ",[21,1005,1006],{},"undefined",", and only then do we \"officially enter\" the assignment step.",[17,1009,1010,1011,1013,1014,1016,1017,1019,1020,1023,1024,1026,1027,1029,1030,1032],{},"Before I explain the \"assignment step,\" keep in mind that ",[21,1012,131],{}," currently points at memory ",[21,1015,895],{},". So ",[21,1018,135],{}," gets reassigned to ",[21,1021,1022],{},"{ y: 1}"," (a new memory slot, ",[21,1025,926],{},"), but ",[21,1028,895],{}," is not freed. Why not? Because the JavaScript engine sees that this memory is still being referenced, so ",[21,1031,895],{}," doesn't get released. From a code perspective it looks like this:",[33,1034,1036],{"className":35,"code":1035,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"a = { y: 1} (0x03);\na(0x01).y = 0x03;\n",[21,1037,1038,1056],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,1039,1040,1042,1044,1046,1048,1051,1053],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,1041,106],{"class":52},[42,1043,56],{"class":48},[42,1045,740],{"class":52},[42,1047,450],{"class":59},[42,1049,1050],{"class":52},"} (",[42,1052,926],{"class":59},[42,1054,1055],{"class":52},");\n",[42,1057,1058,1060,1063,1065,1068,1070,1073],{"class":44,"line":66},[42,1059,135],{"class":215},[42,1061,1062],{"class":52},"(",[42,1064,895],{"class":59},[42,1066,1067],{"class":52},").y ",[42,1069,56],{"class":48},[42,1071,1072],{"class":59}," 0x03",[42,1074,63],{"class":52},[17,1076,1077,1078,1080,1081,144],{},"So the final answer for ",[21,1079,880],{}," is ",[21,1082,1083],{},"{ x: { x:2 } y: { y:1 } }",[17,1085,1086],{},[772,1087],{"alt":1088,"src":1089},"Final answer","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u0